Unless you've been living under a rock for the past week, then you'll have seen that <a href="http://redhat.com" target="" class="regularLink">Red Hat</a> just added support for <a href="http://jboss.org/as7" target="" class="regularLink">JBoss AS 7</a> on <a href="http://openshift.redhat.com" target="" class="regularLink">OpenShift</a> (both Express and Flex).
</p>

